  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "# 1. My Lane (Freestyle)

I am choosing the **AI Referral Opportunity** freestyle lane.

The increasing use of AI assistants such as ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude, and Perplexity is changing how users discover information online. Instead of only searching through traditional search engines, many users now ask AI assistants for answers and follow the recommended links.

My goal is to explore which characteristics of web pages are associated with receiving AI referral traffic and whether those characteristics can be used to identify pages that have strong AI referral potential.

I selected this lane because it focuses on an emerging area of SEO and machine learning. Although this topic has fewer positive examples than traditional search traffic, I believe it is an interesting opportunity to learn about exploratory data analysis, feature engineering, and ranking models while working on a real-world business problem.

Since this is a freestyle lane, my plan is to begin with exploratory analysis, identify patterns in AI referral traffic, and then investigate whether a simple scoring or ranking approach can prioritize pages with the highest AI referral opportunity."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 2. The question: decision, action, cost of a wrong call\n\n*What decision does your work improve? Who acts on it? What does a wrong recommendation cost?*"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "# 2. Research Question

## Research Question

Can the characteristics of a webpage be used to identify pages that have a higher opportunity to receive AI referral traffic?

## Unit of Analysis

The unit of analysis is a single webpage.

## Expected Output

The project will produce an AI Referral Opportunity Score (or ranked list) that estimates which pages are more likely to benefit from optimization for AI-driven referrals.

## Business Decision

If resources are limited, which pages should the SEO or content team prioritize for optimization to improve visibility in AI assistants?

## Action

The content team can review the highest-ranked pages and improve them by updating outdated information, improving structure, adding clearer headings, expanding useful content, improving FAQs where appropriate, and increasing overall content quality.

## Cost of a Wrong Recommendation

False Positive:
A page may be prioritized even though it has little potential to gain AI referral traffic. This wastes time and content resources.

False Negative:
A page with strong AI referral potential may be ignored, causing the business to miss opportunities for additional traffic and visibility.

## Why Machine Learning?

Many characteristics may influence AI referrals simultaneously, including content freshness, engagement, search visibility, page quality, and other features. Machine learning can identify useful patterns across multiple variables more effectively than relying on a single manual rule."
  },
  {
